item.title: CVE-2021-38331|2024-09-17T03:08:30.885Z -- wp-t-wap -- wp-t-wap
item.description: The WP-T-Wap WordPress plugin is vulnerable to Reflected Cross-Site Scripting via the posted parameter found in the ~/wap/writer.php file which allows attackers to inject arbitrary web scripts, in versions up to and including 1.13.2.
